<paragraph blockId="96.[264,992,1525,1587]" box="[264,508,1561,1587]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,442,1561,1587]" captionStart="FIGURES 302–308" captionStartId="97.[264,382,1751,1775]" captionTargetBox="[294,1299,610,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-151@97.[284,1343,591,1724]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURES 302–308. Robustagramma brevicauda sp. nov.: 302, posterior view of male terminalia; 303, lateral view of male terminalia; 304, lateral view of male internal genitalia; 305, male sternite 5; 306, dorsal view of female terminalia; 307, ventral view of female terminalia; 308, spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5049951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5049951/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Figs. 302–308</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[455,500,1561,1587]" captionStart="FIGURES 371–378" captionStartId="117.[264,383,1530,1554]" captionTargetBox="[266,1323,320,1487]" captionTargetId="figure-68@117.[251,1325,307,1504]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 371–378. Robustagramma spp. wings (not to scale): 371, R. biangulatum sp. nov.; 372, R.triangulatum sp. nov.; 373, R. brevicauda sp. nov.; 374, R. cultriforme sp. nov.; 375, R. flavistylum sp. nov.; 376, R. disjunctum sp. nov.; 377, R. acutistylum sp. nov.; 378, R. mirabile sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5049985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5049985/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">373</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[264,1323,1641,1867]" box="[264,1013,1641,1667]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
As described for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cui and Marshall" authorityYear="2005" box="[465,794,1641,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavistylum">
<emphasis box="[465,794,1641,1666]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Robustagramma flavistylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[264,1323,1641,1867]" lastBlockId="97.[264,1323,284,515]" lastPageId="97" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
Body length 
<quantity box="[441,584,1681,1707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Gena and lower frons reddish yellow; face and antenna brown. Postocellar bristle slightly shorter than postvertical bristle. Eye height 
<emphasis box="[1099,1126,1721,1746]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">ca</emphasis>
. 2.2 times genal height. Dorsocentral bristles in 2 postsutural pairs, anterior pair similar in length to middle prescutellar acrostichal bristles. Posterodorsal katepisternal bristle half as long as distance between bristle base and wing base. Wing almost clear. Length of second costal sector 
<emphasis box="[1287,1315,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">ca</emphasis>
. 0.53–0.63X length of third. Distal quarter of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[805,835,296,313]" fontSize="7" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">2+3</subScript>
gradually curved forward (nearly straight in 
<specimenCount box="[294,401,327,353]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[590,693,327,353]" name="Ecuador" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
). Discal cell with a short stump vein CuA 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1182,1192,339,356]" fontSize="7" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">1</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="97.[264,1323,284,515]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
Male terminalia: Sternite 5 twice as long as sternite 4. Dorsomedial length of epandrium 
<emphasis box="[264,291,409,434]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">ca</emphasis>
. 0.4X length of sternite 8. Surstylus mainly setose, with a tapering apex. Cercus exceptionally broad and short, half as long as surstylus. Distiphallus with nodes on dorsal whiplike sclerites. Postgonite with a slightly expanded, convex apex.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5049951" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5049951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5049951/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" startId="97.[264,382,1751,1775]" targetBox="[294,1299,610,1712]" targetPageId="97">
