<emphasis box="[496,798,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Robustagramma brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[806,893,1751,1774]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 302, posterior view of male terminalia; 303, lateral view of male terminalia; 304, lateral view of male internal genitalia; 305, male sternite 5; 306, dorsal view of female terminalia; 307, ventral view of female terminalia; 308, spermathecae.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="98.[264,1323,284,833]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Female terminalia: Sternite 8 reduced to 2 small sclerites. Spermatheca with several wrinkles on distal portion, and a few spicules on basal portion.</paragraph>
